      <item>
        <title>Covariance</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Measures the variance of two data series around their mean values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;Covar(X,Y)=\frac{1}{N}\sum_i{(X_i-\bar{X})(Y_i-\bar{Y})}&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;\bar{X}=\frac{1}{N}*\sum_i{X_i}&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The covariance can be computed incrementally:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;Covar(X)=\bar{X*Y} - (\bar{X}*\bar{Y})&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, we sum all &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;X_i&lt;/script&gt;, &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;Y_i&lt;/script&gt; and all products &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;X_i*Y_i&lt;/script&gt;, then build the
difference of their mean values.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
        <pubDate>Wed, 30 Mar 2016 00:44:01 +0200</pubDate>
        <link>http://codiepp.github.io/Hedge-o-Mat/Hedge-o-Mat/statistics/covariance.html</link>
